Angel's Movie Archive - README

This folder is for my Week 8 Folder Maker App project. My app is a simple movie archive that helps me keep track of movies I own and movies I want to buy later.

Inside this project, there are a few important files:

- OwnedMovies.txt keeps track of movies I already own.
- WishlistMovies.txt keeps track of movies I still want to buy.
- MovieArchive.json saves the movie information in JSON format.
- Module1.vb has the main code for the app.
- MovieInfo.vb has the class used for the movie information.
- Code_Examples.txt has the starter code and TODO comments from the assignment.
- Screenshots show that the app runs and creates the correct files.

The app runs in the console. When it starts, it creates a folder called AngelsMovieArchive on the Desktop. From there, I can add movies I own, add movies to my wishlist, search for movies, and view all saved movies.

When I add a movie, the app saves it into a text file and also into the JSON file. This shows that the app can save information in more than one format.

This is an individual project by Angel Bautista.
